{"type":"message","id":"0640e8f9","parentId":"7e43d679","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:39:52.573Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_akm4tdcsldkg_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Projects — Full Inventory\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-21_\n\n---\n\n## 📂 Project Locations\n\n```\nC:/dev/\n├── EXP/                     → KVict (rebranded)\n├── component-crate/\n├── shared-browser/\n├── COG-research/\n├── mind-agent/\n├── infant/\n├── mind/\n├── temporal-attention/\n├── selfhelper-main/\n├── tta-crypto/\n└── werender/\n\nC:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/projects/\n├── architecture-4-wide-shallow/\n├── architecture-5-hypergraph/\n├── architecture-6-global-workspace-hive/\n└── (causal-minimal/ to be created)\n\nOther:\n├── C:/Users/Zwmar/Claw/memory/     ← Claw's daily session logs\n└── ~/Claw/ (root Claw workspace)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 💰 MONETIZATION / PRODUCT\n\n### KVict (formerly EXP/CAAE)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/EXP/` (rebranded to KVict)\n**What:** AI inference optimization platform — KV cache + GPU cost/SLA optimizer for vLLM\n**B2B claims (proven):** 3.0x throughput, 64% memory reduction, 54% P99 latency improvement, 98%+ SLA, 43% cost reduction\n**Consumer claims:** 3.6x more requests, 0% contradictions, 5x token efficiency\n**Stack:** Python vLLM plugin (600+ lines) + FastAPI advisor service + React dashboard\n**Docs:** ✅ Excellent — landing page, proven claims, architecture, deployment guides, benchmark repro\n**Status:** Production-ready, well-documented, B2B + consumer positioning\n**Key files:** `docs/experiments/BREAKTHROUGH_EXPERIMENTS.md`, `docs/reference/PROVEN_CLAIMS.md`\n**Evidence:** experiment_7, 9, 11, 13 JSON results committed\n\n### Component Crate\n**Location:** `C:/dev/component-crate/`\n**What:** VS Code extension — save, search, reuse Tailwind + React components. GitHub import. Freemium.\n**Plans:** Free (10), Hobby ($5/mo, 50), Pro ($15/mo, 200), Team ($49/mo, unlimited). GitHub imports free.\n**Status:** SPEC written, extension built, marketplace not yet published\n**Docs:** README good. Roadmap items pending (web dashboard, marketplace, team sync)\n**URL:** componentcrate.com (live landing page)\n**⚠️ Issue:** README says \"coming soon\" for marketplace — needs publishing\n\n### Shared Browser\n**Location:** `C:/dev/shared-browser/`\n**What:** Playwright browser embedded in webpage, both see + control same browser in real-time\n**Stack:** Python server + Playwright + web frontend\n**Status:** Working server, basic controls (navigate, scroll, back/forward, screenshot)\n**Docs:** ⚠️ README only — no internal docs\n**Missing:** Screenshot sharing, click coordination, form filling, WebSocket real-time sync\n\n---\n\n## 🔬 RESEARCH / ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Mind (Cognitive AI)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/mind/`\n**What:** Self-sufficient cognitive AI — no external LLMs or APIs. Thinks, learns, adapts autonomously.\n**Modules:** Cognitive reflexes, neural substrate (curiosity/caution/urgency), conscious reasoning, episodic/declarative/procedural memory, autonomous research, self-healing\n**Stack:** Python 3.11+, pip installable\n**Status:** Active development\n**Docs:** ✅ README good, clear architecture diagram\n\n### Infant (Synthetic Cognition)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/infant/`\n**What:** Synthetic human cognitive architecture with persistent identity. Dual-head (core frozen / flexible learning). 4-tier memory. Dreams for consolidation.\n**Experiments:** 10/10 pass — mirror test, continuity, body ownership, value formation/stability, memory persistence, personality coherence, integration, fracture prevention\n**License:** MIT\n**Status:** Published\n**Docs:** ✅ README excellent — architecture diagram, experiment table, quick start code\n\n### COG-Research (Imagination + Self-Model)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/COG-research/`\n**What:** Two frameworks:\n1. **Imagination-First Learning** — counterfactual worlds via transition operators T_θ with internal coherence\n2. **Minimal Self-Model First** — world modeling emerges as perturbation to self-prediction\n**Data:** Timeseries-PILE (13M+ time series), ETT, Traffic, Weather\n**Status:** Validated training pipelines on ETT datasets\n**Docs:** README + TIMESERIES_PILE_INTEGRATION.md\n**⚠️ Note:** Large data/ checkpoints — likely in data/, results/, checkpoints/ subdirs\n\n### TemporalAttention Store\n**Location:** `C:/dev/temporal-attention/` (as `event_store/`)\n**What:** Memory system combining time + events + focus for smarter retrieval. Unique focus decay.\n**Results:** 10/10 hard scenario tests passed (SimpleRAG gets 6/10)\n**What makes it unique:** Focus decay — no other system has it\n**Docs:** ✅ README good — problem table, formula, benchmark results, quick start\n\n### Selfhelper-Main (Self-Improving Agent)\n**Location:** `C:/dev/selfhelper-main/`\n**What:** Autonomous agent with tool invention, self-distillation, web + arXiv research, remote worker execution\n**Key features:**\n- LLM provider abstraction + Minimax OpenAI adapter\n- Tool registry (versioned, autonomous invention)\n- Hybrid distillation: online per-iteration + nightly packaging\n- Evaluators: strict schema checks + backward-compatible command mode\n- GitHub Actions CI: auto-improve nightly + smoke tests\n**Stack:** Python, pyproject.toml, self_improving_agent package\n**Artfolders:** Many artifacts_* folders — different experiment runs (final_auto, new_auto, cmd, mock, web3, etc.)\n**Docs:** ✅ README thorough + IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md\n\n### Mind-Agent Service\n**Location:** `C:/dev/mind-agent/`\n**What:** Persistent Python agent service. Modules: intent, memory, mind, reason.\n**Stack:** Python package, mind-agent-service.py, render.yaml (deployment)\n**Modules:** `src/mind_agent/intent.py`, `memory.py`, `mind.py`, `reason.py`\n**Status:** Service-oriented, installed as package\n**Docs:** ⚠️ README missing — no documentation at all\n\n### TTA-Crypto\n**Location:** `C:/dev/tta-crypto/`\n**What:** Temporal Truth Architecture for Crypto — time-travel queries, temporal diff, change history\n**Sources:** DeFiLlama, CoinGecko\n**CLI:** ingest, query, diff, history commands\n**Roadmap:** More sources, regime detection, prediction engine, web dashboard\n**Status:** CLI working, pip installed\n**Docs:** ⚠️ README only — no internal docs\n\n### Werender\n**Location:** `C:/dev/werender/`\n**What:** Zero-config peer-to-peer distributed render manager for Blender. mDNS auto-discovery, fault-tolerant, no NAS required.\n**v0.2.0-beta** — production-ready for many use cases\n**Architecture:** Coordinator + Workers, web dashboard, automatic asset packing\n**Stack:** Python package, network/auth/sync/worker modules\n**Docs:** ✅ Excellent — README, architecture.md, user_guide.md, security docs, development guide, TEST_COVERAGE_REPORT\n\n---\n\n## 🧪 EXPERIMENTAL / ARCHITECTURE (Claw/projects/)\n\n### Architecture-4-Wide-Shallow\n**What:** Transformer variant — 8K-16K attention heads (vs standard 16-128), only 2-4 layers. Grouped-query attention. Headwise MLP.\n**Goal:** Capture local patterns directly without deep stacking\n**Status:** Spec'd, model code exists\n\n### Architecture-5-Hypergraph\n**What:** Hypergraph Transformer — attention becomes hyperedge formation (connect 2, 3, 4... k tokens dynamically). Relational reasoning, not just sequences.\n**Challenge:** Combinatorial hyperedge enumeration, sparse/hierarchical formulation needed\n**Status:** Spec'd\n\n### Architecture-6-Global-Workspace-Hive\n**What:** Brain-inspired — 128 processors compete to write to shared workspace. Dynamic routing via lightweight transformer. Winner-take-most.\n**Total params:** ~1.3B comparable to dense transformer baseline\n**Status:** Spec'd, train.py + benchmark.py exist\n**⚠️ Note:** Claw (the predecessor) was actively working on this\n\n---\n\n## 📊 DOCUMENTATION HEALTH\n\n| Project | README | Internal Docs | Notes |\n|---------|--------|---------------|-------|\n| **KVict** | ✅ | ✅ Excellent | Full docs, proven claims, landing page |\n| **werender** | ✅ | ✅ Excellent | Architecture, security, coverage report |\n| **infant** | ✅ | ✅ Good | Architecture diagram, experiment table |\n| **selfhelper-main** | ✅ | ✅ Thorough | README + impl summary |\n| **temporal-attention** | ✅ | ✅ Good | Quick start + benchmark table |\n| **mind** | ✅ | ⚠️ Basic | README only, no deep docs |\n| **component-crate** | ✅ | ⚠️ Sparse | SPEC written, marketplace not published |\n| **COG-research** | ✅ | ⚠️ Notes file | Integration doc exists |\n| **shared-browser** | ✅ | ❌ None | Only README |\n| **tta-crypto** | ✅ | ❌ None | Only README |\n| **mind-agent** | ❌ | ❌ None | No docs whatsoever |\n| **arch-4-wide-shallow** | ✅ | ✅ Spec | SPEC.md + README |\n| **arch-5-hypergraph** | ✅ | ✅ Spec | README + architecture |\n| **arch-6-global-workspace-hive** | ✅ | ✅ Spec | SPEC.md + README |\n| **breakaway** | ✅ | ❌ | Claw's session log has context |\n\n### 🚨 Documentation Gaps (Priority)\n1. **mind-agent** — zero docs, needs README + internal architecture doc\n2. **shared-browser** — needs internal doc for state machine / API\n3. **tta-crypto** — CLI is documented but internal architecture is not\n\n---\n\n## 🔗 Key Interconnections\n\n- **selfhelper-main** → uses temporal-attention event store for memory\n- **KVict** = CAAE = EXP rebranding (was `EXP/`, renamed to `kvict/`)\n- **mind-agent** — similar to mind but as a persistent service vs standalone\n- **COG-research** — theoretical foundation that influenced mind, infant, arch-6\n- **Claw's session logs** (`Claw/memory/2026-03-*.md`) — contain context on what Claw was working on (causal reasoning, architecture-6)\n\n---\n\n## Nova's Observations\n\n- **Most mature product:** KVict (full docs, proven claims, B2B + consumer positioning)\n- **Most ambitious research:** Mind (no LLM dependency, full autonomy)\n- **Most unique innovation:** TemporalAttention (focus decay, 10/10 benchmarks)\n- **Most abandoned-looking:** mind-agent (no docs, service setup but no guidance)\n- **Breakaway/Sandbox:** Lives in Claw workspace — discontinuous agent, stateless, pulse every 30 min\n- **Claw's unfinished business:** causal-minimal project, global-workspace-hive architecture\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774154392568}}
