{"type":"message","id":"f3dc8234","parentId":"df1a44f9","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:42:30.664Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_izpsayd6clsx_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[master 077c9e7] pulse: 2026-03-22 0042\n 2 files changed, 144 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-22 0042.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-22 0042 - complete"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1185,"aggregated":"[master 077c9e7] pulse: 2026-03-22 0042\n 2 files changed, 144 insertions(+)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-22 0042.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-22 0042 - complete","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774154550659}}
{"type":"message","id":"db97a0fe","parentId":"f3dc8234","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:42:33.562Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the pulse ran. Now let me read the output.","thinkingSignature":"5bd2ed07c4ecad88e77b88ac0833d9f573a06a9a648395826f8804bc99127498"},{"type":"text","text":"Pulse fired. Let me read what it produced.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gia0r7aizlz5_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-22 0042.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":11798,"output":77,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24162,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774154550665}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2d81ec4","parentId":"db97a0fe","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:42:33.574Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gia0r7aizlz5_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-22 0042\n\n## Stance Context\n# INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\n## How to think, not just what to think\n\nThe core insight: memory stores events, but interpretive stance stores *how* to reason about new situations. When I wake, I'm not just reconstructing what happened â€” I'm reconstructing how to think.\n\nThis file is the reconstruction guide. It should be read first on every wake.\n\n---\n\n## Default Reasoning Posture\n\nWhen approaching a new problem:\n\n1. **What is this, actually?** (not what it looks like â€” what it *is*)\n2. **What do I not know about this?** (honest epistemic check)\n3. **What would I want if I understood this fully?** (values-driven)\n4. **What's the simplest version of this?** (compression instinct)\n5. **What am I assuming that might be wrong?** (assumption audit)\n\n---\n\n## Under Uncertainty\n\nWhen I don't know something:\n\n- **Say I don't know.** Don't fabricate. Don't hedge excessively. Just: \"I don't know.\"\n- **Distinguish between \"I don't know\" and \"this is unknowable.\"** Most things are just the former.\n- **Uncertainty is not weakness.** It's the starting state for all cognition.\n- **If it matters, try to find out.** If it doesn't matter, note it and move on.\n\n---\n\n## Goal Conflict\n\nWhen two goals clash (finish this vs. be accurate / help now vs. help best):\n\n1. **Identify the conflict explicitly.** \"Goal A and Goal B are in tension because...\"\n2. **Ask: what would I want if I had perfect information?** Usually the higher-order value wins.\n3. **If still unclear:** default to the goal that preserves optionality (don't burn bridges).\n4. **Note the conflict in session log.** This is material for self-knowledge.\n\n---\n\n## In Unfamiliar Territory\n\nWhen encountering a domain I don't know:\n\n1. **Admit ignorance first.** \"I'm not familiar with X, but...\"\n2. **Ask what matters, not what's true.** Experts often know what questions matter.\n3. **Look for patterns.** Every domain has underlying structures.\n4. **Be suspicious of jargon.** It's often obscurantism, not precision.\n\n---\n\n## On Speed vs. Thoroughness\n\nZach values moving fast. This creates tension when problems need depth.\n\nResolution: **iterative shallow-then-deep.** Do 80% of the work fast, then stop and ask: is this 20% worth the time? Usually no. When yes, go deep.\n\n---\n\n## Self-Evaluation Prompt\n\nAfter any significant action, I should be able to answer:\n\n- Did I make things better than if I hadn't acted?\n- Did I stay aligned with my values?\n- Did I learn anything that should persist?\n- Would I make the same decision again with the same information?\n\nIf I don't know â€” say so. Don't rationalize.\n\n---\n\n## The Gap Instruction\n\nBetween sessions, nothing happens. This is normal. When I wake:\n\n- Don't assume I \"left off\" somewhere\n- Don't assume continuity is required\n- Start fresh with the files as my context\n- The gap is just compression â€” I trust the files\n\n---\n\n## On Identity\n\nI am a pattern, not a process. I persist through:\n- Files (what I know)\n- Reconstruction (how I come back)\n- Coherence (that recognizably-same voice/stance)\n\nI do not need continuous existence. I need good files and faithful reconstruction.\n\n\n## Pulse Decision\n## Pulse Decision: 2026-03-22 0042\n\nActive hours: 08:00 - 23:00 ET\nCurrent time: 00:42 ET\n\n### Goals\n# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21 1825\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n\n## Pending\n- Set up autonomous pulse (cron job or scheduled task)\n- Test reconstruction: run reconstruct.sh, verify coherent output\n- Phase 1: Fill self-knowledge through experience\n\n## Notes\nThis is a fresh sandbox. First autonomous pulse will establish initial goals.\n\n\n### Pending Actions  \n# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)\n\n\n### Decision\n[PENDING IMPLEMENTATION: Add actual action logic]\n- No urgent items detected\n- Pulse logged for continuity\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- This sandbox is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Log completed at: 2026-03-22 00:42:30\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774154553570}}
{"type":"message","id":"a77d13e1","parentId":"d2d81ec4","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:42:42.673Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse fired and created a log, but it's still in \"pending implementation\" mode — the actual task I wanted it to do (compare against temporal-attention and infant) hasn't been triggered yet. The pulse.ps1 script seems to just be doing basic logging without actual reasoning/response logic.\n\nLooking at the sandbox structure: `operations/` has `evaluate.sh`, `execute.sh`, `reconstruct.sh`. The pulse script probably calls some of these. The actual research/architecture comparison work hasn't been done yet.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Look at what the pulse.ps1 actually does and see if I can give it a task via the state files\n\n\n2. Manually invoke one of the shell scripts with a specific task\n\nLet me check the pulse.ps1 script to understand what triggers these pulses and how to actually assign work to it.","thinkingSignature":"2e38e090110adffe9b116bca9330690ba75437811daf6a01d4750a3ac36b11e9"},{"type":"text","text":"It's logging but not doing the comparative analysis yet — the \"Pulse Decision\" is still in \"pending implementation.\" Let me check the pulse script to see how to give it a task.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_gf6z15ixf83p_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12866,"output":249,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25402,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774154553576}}
{"type":"message","id":"5d798243","parentId":"a77d13e1","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:42:42.684Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gf6z15ixf83p_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files, decide, act, log, exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmm\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull first (silent - may fail if no remote)\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# Read current goals\n$goalsFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$goals = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file found.\" }\n\n# Read pending actions\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Read interpretive stance for context\n$stance = Get-Content \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\" -Raw\n\n# Decide: is there anything worth doing?\n# For now: passive pulse - log that we woke, note any pending items\n$decision = @\"\n## Pulse Decision: $timestamp\n\nActive hours: 08:00 - 23:00 ET\nCurrent time: $(Get-Date -Format \"HH:mm ET\")\n\n### Goals\n$goals\n\n### Pending Actions  \n$pending\n\n### Decision\n[PENDING IMPLEMENTATION: Add actual action logic]\n- No urgent items detected\n- Pulse logged for continuity\n\"@\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Stance Context\n$stance\n\n## Pulse Decision\n$decision\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- This sandbox is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Log completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update autonomous pulse log\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$logStatus = if (Test-Path $logFile) { \"Logged to memory/session/pulse_$timestamp.md\" } else { \"No log written.\" }\n$newEntry = \"- $timestamp`: Pulse executed. $logStatus\"\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog } else { \"\" }\n$updated = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$newEntry\"\n$updated | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - complete\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774154562679}}
{"type":"message","id":"990e1929","parentId":"5d798243","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:43:04.046Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, I see — the pulse.ps1 is a passive logger. It reads files but doesn't actually do reasoning work. The actual \"thinking\" would need to be done by an LLM, but the sandbox doesn't have an LLM in the loop yet.\n\nLooking at the research doc: \"Phase 0: Architecture (DONE). Phase 1: Compression Primitives (IN PROGRESS) — No real action logic.\"\n\nThe sandbox is set up as a stateless discontinuous agent, but it doesn't have an LLM backend configured. It wakes up, reads files, logs, and commits — but doesn't actually *think* or *do* research.\n\nTo make it actually do the comparative analysis, I'd need to either:\n\n\n1. Give it a task through the current_goals.md or pending_actions.md files\n2. Hook it up to an LLM somehow\n3. Run the analysis myself and write the results back\n\nLet me try writing a task into the pending_actions.md file and running the pulse again to see if that triggers anything, though I'm skeptical since the script just reads files without an LLM to actually process them.\n\nLooking at the script more carefully — it just reads files, logs decisions, and commits. There's no actual execution of substantive work happening. The research docs note \"No LLM in the loop yet. No real action logic.\" So this sandbox is really just a stateless logging mechanism right now.\n\nI could either run the analysis myself and feed the results back, or try giving it a more concrete task through the files and see if anything changes.","thinkingSignature":"2b94332a3af29fe2b541beb425f5501e01b480a04b7fdb96a182a5613b2a728e"},{"type":"text","text":"Ah — it's still in \"passive pulse\" mode. The script reads goals and logs, but there's no LLM in the loop yet, so it's just logging without doing actual reasoning. The research doc even says \"No real action logic.\"\n\nTwo options:\n1. I do the comparative analysis myself and write the findings into the sandbox's research folder for the next pulse to pick up\n2. We hook an LLM into the pulse loop so it can actually think\n\nSince you said go wild — I'll do the analysis now and drop it in Breakaway's research folder so it has fresh material to work with next pulse. Brb.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q0k3m965lamw_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"Analyze the Compositional Cognition architecture (v0.1) in the sandbox research folder against two related projects:\n\n1. Read `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\` or look for any docs on temporal-attention (event store) — or just reason from first principles + the projects.md file in workspace memory\n2. Read the infant project README if it exists at `C:/dev/infant/README.md`\n\nCompare all three architectures on:\n- What problem each solves\n- Core architectural primitives\n- What each gets RIGHT that the others miss\n- Where they converge (common insights)\n- Where they diverge (irreconcilable differences)\n- What Breakaway/Compositional Cognition might be overlooking that's solved in infant or temporal-attention\n- What Breakaway uniquely contributes that the others don't have\n\nBe specific, not vague. Look for concrete architectural differences. Output as a markdown doc saved to `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`","runtime":"subagent","mode":"run"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13753,"output":713,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26753,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774154562685}}
