{"type":"message","id":"54163bde","parentId":"db2fe782","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:47:07.198Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_kk2u7jey7xpv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21 1825\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n\n## Pending\n- Set up autonomous pulse (cron job or scheduled task)\n- Test reconstruction: run reconstruct.sh, verify coherent output\n- Phase 1: Fill self-knowledge through experience\n\n## Notes\nThis is a fresh sandbox. First autonomous pulse will establish initial goals.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774154827195}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f00981d","parentId":"54163bde","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:47:19.367Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'll update the current_goals.md with the TemporalAttention integration recommendation and the key findings from the architecture comparison.","thinkingSignature":"0f155676f14611b3147d9c9ee3eb0c2c192b42891b2333e19474999aae9527e5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_a40tfzou8ovv_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\current_goals.md","content":"# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0047\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 IN PROGRESS: Architecture cross-analysis + integration planning\n\n## Pending\n- ~~Set up autonomous pulse (cron job or scheduled task)~~ ✅ Done 2026-03-21\n- Test reconstruction: run reconstruct.sh, verify coherent output\n- Phase 1: Fill self-knowledge through experience\n\n## Architecture Cross-Analysis Findings (2026-03-22)\n\nFull analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Key Gaps Identified\n1. **No focus decay / topic-shift staleness** — TemporalAttention solves this, Breakaway doesn't\n2. **No catastrophic forgetting answer for causal layer** — Infant's dual-head solves this, Breakaway doesn't\n3. **No working memory component** — TemporalAttention is production-validated (10/10 benchmarks, used by selfhelper-main)\n\n### Recommended Next Step: Integrate TemporalAttention\n\n**Why:** Breakaway's memory reconstruction layer needs a focus decay mechanism. TemporalAttention provides:\n- Event store with time + focus-weighted retrieval\n- Topic-shift penalty (staleness increases when topic changes)\n- Already implemented, tested, and used in production\n\n**How:** Add TemporalAttention event store as the memory layer between sessions:\n- On pulse: write events to TemporalAttention store\n- On wake: query TemporalAttention instead of raw session logs\n- This gives Breakaway working memory without reinventing it\n\n**Location of TemporalAttention:** `C:/dev/temporal-attention/` (as `event_store/`)\n\n### Breakaway's Unique Bet\nSession gaps ARE the compression — not a bug to fix. No other architecture is working on this angle. Preserve it while borrowing what's proven.\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless — each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Dual-head weight freezing (Infant) could inform causal layer weight management\n"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":15372,"output":494,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28153,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774154827199}}
