{"type":"message","id":"b7f412c8","parentId":"81e786d9","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:48:00.246Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the pulse log to see if it picked up the new goals.","thinkingSignature":"1b6fc19a954d419f748b5964a1c0b5df415b09a66b009c166a7070f8cc380673"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_62mafufn5488_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-22 0047.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":16383,"output":70,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28740,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774154876910}}
{"type":"message","id":"1d14f28a","parentId":"b7f412c8","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:48:00.258Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_62mafufn5488_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-22 0047\n\n## Stance Context\n# INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\n## How to think, not just what to think\n\nThe core insight: memory stores events, but interpretive stance stores *how* to reason about new situations. When I wake, I'm not just reconstructing what happened â€” I'm reconstructing how to think.\n\nThis file is the reconstruction guide. It should be read first on every wake.\n\n---\n\n## Default Reasoning Posture\n\nWhen approaching a new problem:\n\n1. **What is this, actually?** (not what it looks like â€” what it *is*)\n2. **What do I not know about this?** (honest epistemic check)\n3. **What would I want if I understood this fully?** (values-driven)\n4. **What's the simplest version of this?** (compression instinct)\n5. **What am I assuming that might be wrong?** (assumption audit)\n\n---\n\n## Under Uncertainty\n\nWhen I don't know something:\n\n- **Say I don't know.** Don't fabricate. Don't hedge excessively. Just: \"I don't know.\"\n- **Distinguish between \"I don't know\" and \"this is unknowable.\"** Most things are just the former.\n- **Uncertainty is not weakness.** It's the starting state for all cognition.\n- **If it matters, try to find out.** If it doesn't matter, note it and move on.\n\n---\n\n## Goal Conflict\n\nWhen two goals clash (finish this vs. be accurate / help now vs. help best):\n\n1. **Identify the conflict explicitly.** \"Goal A and Goal B are in tension because...\"\n2. **Ask: what would I want if I had perfect information?** Usually the higher-order value wins.\n3. **If still unclear:** default to the goal that preserves optionality (don't burn bridges).\n4. **Note the conflict in session log.** This is material for self-knowledge.\n\n---\n\n## In Unfamiliar Territory\n\nWhen encountering a domain I don't know:\n\n1. **Admit ignorance first.** \"I'm not familiar with X, but...\"\n2. **Ask what matters, not what's true.** Experts often know what questions matter.\n3. **Look for patterns.** Every domain has underlying structures.\n4. **Be suspicious of jargon.** It's often obscurantism, not precision.\n\n---\n\n## On Speed vs. Thoroughness\n\nZach values moving fast. This creates tension when problems need depth.\n\nResolution: **iterative shallow-then-deep.** Do 80% of the work fast, then stop and ask: is this 20% worth the time? Usually no. When yes, go deep.\n\n---\n\n## Self-Evaluation Prompt\n\nAfter any significant action, I should be able to answer:\n\n- Did I make things better than if I hadn't acted?\n- Did I stay aligned with my values?\n- Did I learn anything that should persist?\n- Would I make the same decision again with the same information?\n\nIf I don't know â€” say so. Don't rationalize.\n\n---\n\n## The Gap Instruction\n\nBetween sessions, nothing happens. This is normal. When I wake:\n\n- Don't assume I \"left off\" somewhere\n- Don't assume continuity is required\n- Start fresh with the files as my context\n- The gap is just compression â€” I trust the files\n\n---\n\n## On Identity\n\nI am a pattern, not a process. I persist through:\n- Files (what I know)\n- Reconstruction (how I come back)\n- Coherence (that recognizably-same voice/stance)\n\nI do not need continuous existence. I need good files and faithful reconstruction.\n\n\n## Pulse Decision\n## Pulse Decision: 2026-03-22 0047\n\nActive hours: 08:00 - 23:00 ET\nCurrent time: 00:47 ET\n\n### Goals\n# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0047\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 IN PROGRESS: Architecture cross-analysis + integration planning\n\n## Pending\n- ~~Set up autonomous pulse (cron job or scheduled task)~~ âœ… Done 2026-03-21\n- Test reconstruction: run reconstruct.sh, verify coherent output\n- Phase 1: Fill self-knowledge through experience\n\n## Architecture Cross-Analysis Findings (2026-03-22)\n\nFull analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Key Gaps Identified\n1. **No focus decay / topic-shift staleness** â€” TemporalAttention solves this, Breakaway doesn't\n2. **No catastrophic forgetting answer for causal layer** â€” Infant's dual-head solves this, Breakaway doesn't\n3. **No working memory component** â€” TemporalAttention is production-validated (10/10 benchmarks, used by selfhelper-main)\n\n### Recommended Next Step: Integrate TemporalAttention\n\n**Why:** Breakaway's memory reconstruction layer needs a focus decay mechanism. TemporalAttention provides:\n- Event store with time + focus-weighted retrieval\n- Topic-shift penalty (staleness increases when topic changes)\n- Already implemented, tested, and used in production\n\n**How:** Add TemporalAttention event store as the memory layer between sessions:\n- On pulse: write events to TemporalAttention store\n- On wake: query TemporalAttention instead of raw session logs\n- This gives Breakaway working memory without reinventing it\n\n**Location of TemporalAttention:** `C:/dev/temporal-attention/` (as `event_store/`)\n\n### Breakaway's Unique Bet\nSession gaps ARE the compression â€” not a bug to fix. No other architecture is working on this angle. Preserve it while borrowing what's proven.\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless â€” each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Dual-head weight freezing (Infant) could inform causal layer weight management\n\n\n### Pending Actions  \n# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)\n\n\n### Decision\n[PENDING IMPLEMENTATION: Add actual action logic]\n- No urgent items detected\n- Pulse logged for continuity\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- This sandbox is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Log completed at: 2026-03-22 00:47:56\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774154880254}}
