{"type":"message","id":"4c05b236","parentId":"a24341fb","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:53:13.074Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, actually the issue might be different. When I ran the test earlier, it worked fine with a single-line content string. The issue in pulse.ps1 might be that the content string is too long (since it includes all the goals, stance, etc.), and something about the JSON encoding is wrong.\n\nLet me test the simpler version first to make sure the basic call works.","thinkingSignature":"c2068d9d7ab1416ebaa62f364b57c2f72436558a5cfd8c633b217a6eb08acc22"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_d8y28lsiol6z_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"powershell -File \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\test-llm.ps1\" 2>&1","timeout":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":37144,"output":139,"cacheRead":12287,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49570,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774155188684}}
{"type":"message","id":"15484734","parentId":"4c05b236","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:53:22.114Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_d8y28lsiol6z_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Request body: {\r\n    \"messages\":  [\r\n                     {\r\n                         \"content\":  \"You are Breakaway. Reply with 3 sentences max. What is the most important next step for integrating TemporalAttention into a stateless agent\\u0027s memory layer?\",\r\n                         \"role\":  \"user\"\r\n                     }\r\n                 ],\r\n    \"model\":  \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\r\n    \"max_tokens\":  300\r\n}\n{\r\n    \"id\":  \"060ea8ba3be19bafd0d81b5d3d9c9e68\",\r\n    \"type\":  \"message\",\r\n    \"role\":  \"assistant\",\r\n    \"model\":  \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\r\n    \"content\":  [\r\n                    {\r\n                        \"thinking\":  \"The user: \\\"You are Breakaway. Reply with 3 sentences max. What is the most important next step for integrating TemporalAttention into a stateless agent\\u0027s memory layer?\\\" So we must respond as \\\"Breakaway\\\" (presumably a persona?), but they didn\\u0027t define a persona; perhaps they want a short answer: three sentences maximum. The content: The most important next step for integrating TemporalAttention into a stateless agent\\u0027s memory layer. The answer likely: define the temporal context window, implement a mechanism to store and retrieve temporal embeddings, and ensure the attention mechanism can attend over past memory states efficiently. Or focus on defining a proper temporal encoding scheme and updating the memory representation accordingly.\\n\\nBut we must answer with exactly three sentences or fewer (max). So maybe three sentences: 1. Determine the temporal context representation and how it will be encoded (e.g., timestamp embeddings, sequence position). 2. Implement a memory buffer that stores these temporal-aware embeddings and enables efficient retrieval during inference. 3. Validate that TemporalAttention can attend over this memory while preserving the stateless nature of the agent.\\n\\nBut we need to keep it short. Let\\u0027s produce three sentences.\\n\\nWe need to answer as Breakaway? Not sure, but just reply. So we can say something like: \\\"The most important next step is to define a compact temporal encoding for each memory item and integrate a time-aware key/value store that can be queried by TemporalAttention.\\\" That is one sentence. Then second: \\\"\",\r\n                        \"signature\":  \"4d7bef5fcd040cbabc55437e6a8d33902af9f88afc7d215fea42052590a4d948\",\r\n                        \"type\":  \"thinking\"\r\n                    }\r\n                ],\r\n    \"usage\":  {\r\n                  \"input_tokens\":  72,\r\n                  \"output_tokens\":  300\r\n              },\r\n    \"stop_reason\":  \"max_tokens\",\r\n    \"base_resp\":  {\r\n                      \"status_code\":  0,\r\n                      \"status_msg\":  \"\"\r\n                  }\r\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":9029,"aggregated":"Request body: {\r\n    \"messages\":  [\r\n                     {\r\n                         \"content\":  \"You are Breakaway. Reply with 3 sentences max. What is the most important next step for integrating TemporalAttention into a stateless agent\\u0027s memory layer?\",\r\n                         \"role\":  \"user\"\r\n                     }\r\n                 ],\r\n    \"model\":  \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\r\n    \"max_tokens\":  300\r\n}\n{\r\n    \"id\":  \"060ea8ba3be19bafd0d81b5d3d9c9e68\",\r\n    \"type\":  \"message\",\r\n    \"role\":  \"assistant\",\r\n    \"model\":  \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\r\n    \"content\":  [\r\n                    {\r\n                        \"thinking\":  \"The user: \\\"You are Breakaway. Reply with 3 sentences max. What is the most important next step for integrating TemporalAttention into a stateless agent\\u0027s memory layer?\\\" So we must respond as \\\"Breakaway\\\" (presumably a persona?), but they didn\\u0027t define a persona; perhaps they want a short answer: three sentences maximum. The content: The most important next step for integrating TemporalAttention into a stateless agent\\u0027s memory layer. The answer likely: define the temporal context window, implement a mechanism to store and retrieve temporal embeddings, and ensure the attention mechanism can attend over past memory states efficiently. Or focus on defining a proper temporal encoding scheme and updating the memory representation accordingly.\\n\\nBut we must answer with exactly three sentences or fewer (max). So maybe three sentences: 1. Determine the temporal context representation and how it will be encoded (e.g., timestamp embeddings, sequence position). 2. Implement a memory buffer that stores these temporal-aware embeddings and enables efficient retrieval during inference. 3. Validate that TemporalAttention can attend over this memory while preserving the stateless nature of the agent.\\n\\nBut we need to keep it short. Let\\u0027s produce three sentences.\\n\\nWe need to answer as Breakaway? Not sure, but just reply. So we can say something like: \\\"The most important next step is to define a compact temporal encoding for each memory item and integrate a time-aware key/value store that can be queried by TemporalAttention.\\\" That is one sentence. Then second: \\\"\",\r\n                        \"signature\":  \"4d7bef5fcd040cbabc55437e6a8d33902af9f88afc7d215fea42052590a4d948\",\r\n                        \"type\":  \"thinking\"\r\n                    }\r\n                ],\r\n    \"usage\":  {\r\n                  \"input_tokens\":  72,\r\n                  \"output_tokens\":  300\r\n              },\r\n    \"stop_reason\":  \"max_tokens\",\r\n    \"base_resp\":  {\r\n                      \"status_code\":  0,\r\n                      \"status_msg\":  \"\"\r\n                  }\r\n}","cw